@@mEGOMANCER@@W

@@mHistory@@W
  Egomancers emerged from within the Psionicist tradition itself, specifically
  from the Assertion Wing: a school of thought that argued the mind's primary
  power lay not in perception or communication but in imposition. Early
  Assertionists developed techniques for overriding external cognitive
  processes, bending probability through focused intent, and sustaining
  mental pressure across extended engagements rather than delivering single
  decisive bursts. Their methods were considered extreme by conservative
  academies and several Assertion teachers were expelled. The expelled faculty
  simply founded independent schools. Psionicists who return through the
  mortal path and commit to the imposition doctrine become Egomancers --
  practitioners of the Assertion Wing's full and unfettered philosophy.

Egomancers bend force of will into weaponized cognition. They do not overpower
through brute spell volume, but through pressure, disruption, and focused mindfire.

